	PAYMENT_STOP__PAYM_STOP_TYPE
	{
		/* Specifies the reason why a Payment Stop is requested.
When an inward MT111 generates a payment stop record, payment stop type 99 is used.
Validation Rules


1 or 2 numeric character Payment Stop Type code. Multivalue Field associated with Fields 2 to   24. (Mandatory input) It must be a valid code on the PAYMENT.STOP.TYPE table. */
		PAYM_STOP_TYPE -> CHQ_PaymentStop:PAYMENT_STOP_TYPE
			@t24:i (align=L, inputBehaviour=I, maxLength=30, sysNumber=2.0, core=true, businessType=A, t24Name=PAYM.STOP.TYPE)
		/* Identifies the first in a range or, if LAST CHEQUE NO (Field 4) is not entered, the only Cheque Number which is being stopped.
This field is used to specify the number of the cheque to be stopped. It can also be used in conjunction with LAST CHEQUE NUMBER (Field 4) to define a range of cheques to be stopped. When a cheque number input in DATA.CAPTURE, FUNDS.TRANSFER or TELLER matches a cheque number defined in this table, an override will be given stating that there is a stop on either the cheque number or amount.  You have the option to confirm these overrides to continue processing.


Validation Rules
Up to 16 numeric characters. Multivalue Field associated with Fields 2 to 24. (Optional input. No default value.)
This field must not start or end with a / and must not contain two consecutive slashes // (SWIFT Error Code T26).
Mandatory input if RAISE.ACTIVITY field is set to "Yes", otherwise optional input. */
		FIRST_CHEQUE_NO : mml:Integer
			@t24:i (align=R, inputBehaviour=I, maxLength=35, sysNumber=3.0, core=true, t24Name=FIRST.CHEQUE.NO)
		/* Identifies the Last Cheque Number in a range to be stopped.
This field in conjunction with FIRST CHEQUE NUMBER (Field 3) is used to define a range of cheques to be stopped. When a cheque number input in DATA.CAPTURE, FUNDS.TRANSFER or TELLER matches a cheque number defined in this table, an override will be given stating that there is a stop on either the cheque number or amount.  You have the option to confirm these overrides to continue processing.
Validation Rules


Up to 16 numeric characters. Multivalue Field associated with Fields 2 to   24. [Optional input when FIRST CHEQUE NO (Field 3) has been input. Otherwise no input is allowed. No default value.] LAST CHEQUE NO must exceed FIRST CHEQUE NO (Field   3).
This field should be left Blank if the RAISE.ACTIVITY field is to be set to "Yes" i.e. if a SWIFT Message (MT112) is to be raised.
SWIFT MT112 can only be raised for a Single Cheque. */
		LAST_CHEQUE_NO : mml:Integer
			@t24:i (align=R, inputBehaviour=I, maxLength=35, sysNumber=4.0, core=true, t24Name=LAST.CHEQUE.NO)
		/* This is a no input field and holds the exact no. of cheque leaves to be stopped .
Validation Rules


No input field. Multi value field associated with fields 2 to 24. */
		NO_OF_LEAVES : mml:Integer
			@t24:i (align=R, inputBehaviour=N, maxLength=3, sysNumber=5.0, core=true, t24Name=NO.OF.LEAVES)
		/* Identifies the type of cheques which are to be stopped.
Examples are EC for Eurocheques, SC for Standard Cheques, CC for Customised Cheques etc.
Validation Rules


Up to 2 type A (Alphanumeric) character Cheque Type code.
Multivalue Field associated with Fields 2 to 24.
If cheque type  is exists in CHEQUE.TYPE.ACCOUNT for the account,     then cheque type will be defaulted based on the Cheque No.
Mandatory input if FIRST CHEQUE NO (Field 3) is defined and     Cheque.Register is set as "YES" in ACCOUNT.PARAMETER
Otherwise optional input
If entered must be a existing code on the CHEQUE.TYPE table */
		CHEQUE_TYPE -> CHQ_Config:CHEQUE_TYPE
			@t24:i (align=L, inputBehaviour=I, maxLength=4, sysNumber=6.0, core=true, businessType=SSS, t24Name=CHEQUE.TYPE)
		/* Specifies the date on which the Payment Stop is placed.
Note:


It is important to note that, whichever date is input in this field the stop payment will always be 'effective' as soon as it has been input and authorised.
This field must be after DATE.OF.ISSUE and before ACTION.DATE.
This field does not accept forward dates.


Validation Rules
Up to 9 type D date characters (Date format in range 1950 to 2049). Multivalue Field associated with Fields 2 to 24. (Optional input. Default to System Date.) */
		STOP_DATE : T24BusinessTypes:D
			@t24:i (align=R, inputBehaviour=I, maxLength=11, sysNumber=7.0, core=true, t24Name=STOP.DATE)
		/* Specifies the Amount From which the Payment Stop is effective.
This field is used, to specify the amount of the cheque(s) which are to be stopped. If AMOUNT TO (Field 9) is also input, then all cheques with amounts between or equal to the two values will be warned on-line as suspect stopped cheques and will request an override message.


Validation Rules
Up to 12 type AMT (Standard Amount Format) characters plus a decimal point. Multivalue Field associated with Fields 2 to 24.
Mandatory input if:


CHEQUE.NO (Field 3) is not defined or
RAISE.ACTIVITY field is set to "Yes".
Otherwise optional input. No Default Value. */
		AMOUNT_FROM : T24BusinessTypes:AMT
			@t24:i (align=R, inputBehaviour=I, maxLength=19, sysNumber=8.0, core=true, t24Name=AMOUNT.FROM, typeModifiers="1")
		/* Specifies the Amount up To which the Payment Stop is effective.
This Field is used, in conjunction with AMOUNT FROM (Field 8) to specify the amount of the cheque(s) which are to be stopped. All cheques with amounts between or equal to the two values will be warned on-line as suspect stopped cheques and will request an override message.
Validation Rules


Up to 12 type AMT (Standard Amount Format) characters plus a decimal point. Multivalue Field associated with Fields 2 to   24. [Optional input when AMOUNT FROM (Field 8) entered, otherwise not allowed. No default value.] It Must be greater than AMOUNT FROM (Field   8).
This field should be left Blank if the RAISE.ACTIVITY field is to be set to "Yes" i.e. if a SWIFT Message (MT112) is to be raised.
SWIFT MT112 can only be raised for a Single Amount. */
		AMOUNT_TO : T24BusinessTypes:AMT
			@t24:i (align=R, inputBehaviour=I, maxLength=19, sysNumber=9.0, core=true, t24Name=AMOUNT.TO, typeModifiers="1")
		/* This is a no input field . When a stop payment is input and authorized this field is set to 'YES' so that the details of the authorized stop payment may not be changed and the charges do not get defaulted again for this multivalue set .
Validation Rules


No input field. Multi value field associated with fields 2 to 24.
